                     Installation
                    ==============

Requirements for Unix/Linux:
----------------------------
1. You need a standard GNU development environment with
   a) C compiler (for example the GNU C Compiler gcc)
   b) gettext
2. Python >= 2.3.1 from http://www.python.org/
3. Python Imaging Library (PIL) from http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/
4. Python Crypto Module from http://www.amk.ca/python/code/crypto.html

Requirements for Windows:
-------------------------
Direct download links are in brackets.
1. Install the MinGW suite from http://mingw.sourceforge.net.
   Be sure to install in the given order:
   a) MingGW
     [ http://osdn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/MinGW-3.1.0-1.exe ]
   b) MSYS
     [ http://osdn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/MSYS-1.0.9.exe ]
   c) libiconv
     [ http://osdn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/libiconv-1.8.0-2003.02.01-1.exe ]
   d) gettext
     [ http://osdn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/gettext-0.11.5-2003.02.01-1.exe ]
2. Install Python >= 2.3.1 from http://www.python.org/
   [ http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.3.2/Python-2.3.2-1.exe ]
3. Install Python for Windows Extensions from
   http://starship.python.net/crew/mhammond/
   [ http://starship.python.net/crew/mhammond/downloads/win32all-163.exe ]
4. Install Python Imaging Library (PIL) from
   http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/
   [ http://www.pythonware.net/storage/PIL-1.1.4.win32-py2.3.exe ]
5. Download Python Crypto Module from
   http://www.amk.ca/python/code/crypto.html
   [ http://www.amk.ca/files/python/crypto/pycrypto-1.9a6.tar.gz ]
   For Installation of PyCrypto see below.

Optional requirements (all platforms)
-------------------------------------
For faster code execution you can install psyco from
http://psyco.sourceforge.net/
[ http://osdn.dl.sourceforge.net/psyco/psyco-1.1.1-win-2.3.zip ]
[ http://osdn.dl.sourceforge.net/psyco/psyco-1.1.1-linux.i386-2.3.tar.gz ]

Setup for Unix/Linux:
---------------------
Run "./configure; make" to compile the included C libraries.
Run "python setup.py build" to compile the Python files.
The CC environment variable is checked before compilation, so you can
change the default C compiler with "export CC=myccompiler".
Run "python setup.py install" to install everything.
Note: if you work from CVS, you must run "./autogen.sh" first to
generate the configure and Makefile files.

Setup for Windows:
------------------
1. Preparing Python for the MinGW compiler
   Search the file python23.dll in your windows folder.
   After you found it, launch MSYS and do:
   % pexports python23.dll > python23.def
   Then use the dlltool
   % dlltool --dllname python23.dll --def python23.def --output-lib libpython23.a
   The resulting library has to be placed in the same directory as
   python23.lib. (Should be the libs directory under your Python installation
   directory.)
3. Compile the JavaScript library
   First, copy the webcleaner-X.X.tar.gz into your MSYS home directory,
   which is usually under c:\msys\1.0\home\user\.
   Launch MSYS and extract the tarball:
   % tar xzvf webcleaner-X.X.tar.gz
   Change into the generated directory:
   % cd webcleaner-X.X
   Configure and compile the JavaScript library:
   % ./configure; make
4. Compile and install PyCrypto
   Close the MSYS application and open a DOS command prompt.
   Change to the pycrypto-1.9a6 directory and do:
   c:> python setup.py build -c mingw32 install
5. Compile and install the Python modules
   Change to the webcleaner-X.X directory and do:
   c:> python setup.py build -c mingw32 install
